body: You database on disk is corrupt. Obviously, that shouldn't happen. It can be "fixed" by removing the "index" directory inside the syncthing configuration directory, but obviously I'm interested in what happened. You say it aborted with an error during indexing. What was that error?

Are you sure there is no message before the panic: xdr read: EOF line?
I had a similar issue but it said 'too many open files'.

Sure, it's all.

Even i had do the complete procedure (delete config files and start syncthing) again. But this time i started it from the console, so i have the complete error output from Syncthing during it worked. 
After two and a half minute i interrupted Syncthing, because it produced much error-text. After interruption, i tried again to start Syncthing. It came the same problem, which i described in my first entry.

I have shorten the output, because the error repeated until i interrupted Syncthing.
